\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 Catalyst of Secrecy\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 Why secrecy?
\f3\b0  Because secrecy separates appetite from accountability. Desire divorced from community becomes demand. In secrecy, your mind builds a private theater; in the light, your heart builds a faithful life. Secrecy tells you, \'93You\'92re managing it.\'94 The gospel tells you, \'93It\'92s managing you.\'94\
Secrecy also shrinks people. In the shadows, a person becomes a part; a name becomes a notch; a covenant becomes a convenience. Secrecy does to lust what comparison does to envy\'97it fertilizes it. 
\f1\i (You used this same \'93catalyst\'94 move with Envy\'97there it was comparison; here it\'92s secrecy.)
\f3\i0 \

\f0\b Illustration:
\f3\b0  Think of a river at night. In daylight you see the current and respect its pull. In the dark, the same river seems still\'97until you step in. Secrecy turns a current into a trap.\

\f0\b TRANSITION:
